WEBVTT

00:02.970 --> 00:07.373
♪

00:07.508 --> 00:09.307
Adult mark:<i> Nothing</i>
<i> made me feel better</i>

00:09.343 --> 00:11.243
<i> Than feeling sick</i>
<i> on a school day.</i>

00:11.245 --> 00:14.212
Big news for this little town...

00:14.281 --> 00:16.582
Tina turner
is gonna pay a visit.

00:16.584 --> 00:19.318
Oh, give me that!

00:19.320 --> 00:21.586
Never thought I'd get
to cover a papal visit.

00:21.622 --> 00:24.722
You know, there's money
to be made from this visit.

00:24.759 --> 00:26.892
Jesus, mary, and joseph.
Have some respect.

00:26.961 --> 00:30.462
[phone ringing]

00:32.933 --> 00:34.266
Hello?

00:34.401 --> 00:35.734
Voice: [on phone]
mike...

00:35.869 --> 00:38.603
Look, I told you
not to call me at home.

00:38.639 --> 00:40.606
-Thank you, goodbye.
-[hangs up phone]

00:40.608 --> 00:41.807
-[coughing]
-telemarketer?

00:41.809 --> 00:42.875
Ah, yeah.

00:43.010 --> 00:45.210
Where's your uniform?

00:45.345 --> 00:47.179
I'm sick!

00:47.248 --> 00:49.247
-I am not buyin' it.
-What?

00:49.316 --> 00:50.849
Adult mark:<i> I first</i>
<i> caught the acting bug</i>

00:50.851 --> 00:51.750
<i> By faking sick...</i>

00:51.885 --> 00:53.685
<i> A lot.</i>

00:53.754 --> 00:58.357
♪

00:58.359 --> 00:59.758
♪

00:59.760 --> 01:01.559
Breathe in.

01:01.595 --> 01:02.828
Out.

01:02.963 --> 01:04.829
[coughs]

01:04.865 --> 01:06.965
Mary: Well?

01:07.034 --> 01:08.901
He's faking.

01:09.036 --> 01:10.636
You little shagger!

01:10.638 --> 01:11.904
But I'm actually sick this time!

01:12.039 --> 01:12.871
Get dressed!

01:12.940 --> 01:14.640
Adult mark:<i> It was</i>
<i> my own fault.</i>

01:14.775 --> 01:16.775
<i> I was the boy who cried</i>
<i> whooping cough.</i>

01:16.777 --> 01:19.378
Mary: Go on.

01:19.380 --> 01:21.246
Little faker.

01:21.381 --> 01:22.647
Jeez!

01:24.852 --> 01:27.252
Sister rose: Our school
has been invited

01:27.387 --> 01:29.555
To send a class to see

01:29.690 --> 01:32.924
His holiness.

01:32.993 --> 01:35.861
I've decided that
this class is...

01:35.930 --> 01:37.495
The least worst.

01:37.531 --> 01:39.331
Congratulations.

01:39.333 --> 01:40.866
One of you will
get to do a reading

01:41.001 --> 01:42.734
In front of the pope himself.

01:42.803 --> 01:44.536
And it will be televised!

01:44.671 --> 01:45.871
Adult mark:<i> Television?!</i>

01:45.873 --> 01:48.473
Any volunteers?

01:48.476 --> 01:51.343
[heavenly music]

01:51.412 --> 01:54.946
Lord, hear our prayer!

01:54.948 --> 01:58.016
Unless it's for the bruins
to win, am I right?

01:58.018 --> 01:59.284
-[audience cheering]
-yeah!

01:59.419 --> 02:00.485
[god laughing]

02:00.488 --> 02:01.887
My man!

02:01.889 --> 02:05.824
[applause]

02:05.959 --> 02:07.559
Ms. Fowler: Mark critch.

02:07.561 --> 02:09.694
The winner by default.

02:09.730 --> 02:14.099
Thank you, miss--
[coughing]

02:14.101 --> 02:16.635
Are you sick, mr. Critch?

02:16.637 --> 02:17.969
Uh, no.
[laughs nervously]

02:18.038 --> 02:21.907
Just gotta lay off
the second-hand smokes.

02:21.909 --> 02:23.642
Adult mark:<i> I had</i>
<i> faked sick before,</i>

02:23.644 --> 02:25.844
<i> But now I had to fake healthy.</i>

02:25.846 --> 02:27.779
[coughs quietly]

02:27.848 --> 02:31.716
♪

02:35.489 --> 02:36.788
Ahem!

02:36.857 --> 02:40.325
Oh, hey!
There he is!

02:40.460 --> 02:41.560
What?

02:41.629 --> 02:43.462
You told me to stop calling you!

02:43.464 --> 02:44.529
Adult mark:<i> Scott howell.</i>

02:44.598 --> 02:46.998
<i> Owner of rival station voaq.</i>

02:47.067 --> 02:48.733
<i> His station was number one,</i>

02:48.769 --> 02:50.902
<i> But first was</i>
<i> never good enough.</i>

02:50.904 --> 02:52.404
Now how'd you get past gertie?

02:52.539 --> 02:55.908
I'm not used to hearing "no."

02:56.043 --> 02:58.477
What's it gonna take

02:58.479 --> 03:00.612
To get you to
come work for me?

03:00.648 --> 03:02.447
I'm not a dj, mr. Howell,

03:02.449 --> 03:04.682
And voaq isn't exactly
known for news, so...

03:04.718 --> 03:08.820
No, no, no, we want you to bring
your call-in segment to us.

03:08.889 --> 03:11.789
And then we'll make it sexier.

03:11.825 --> 03:14.426
I'm not "sexy," mr. Howell.

03:14.495 --> 03:16.027
You don't say!

03:16.063 --> 03:17.462
The world's goin' digital.

03:17.598 --> 03:18.763
It's 1988.

03:18.799 --> 03:20.565
Look at all this crap!

03:20.634 --> 03:22.534
It's a joke!

03:22.536 --> 03:25.036
I'm a "dance with the one
who brought ya" kind of man.

03:25.072 --> 03:26.905
Yeah, which is why
you're stuck here

03:26.974 --> 03:30.642
In this closet for a studio,
with gum under the desk.

03:30.678 --> 03:32.310
I get what I want, mike.

03:35.983 --> 03:37.982
I even get what I don't want.

03:44.591 --> 03:46.325
I've got a show to do,
mr. Howell,

03:46.460 --> 03:47.726
So if you do not mind...

03:47.728 --> 03:49.628
Hey, dad, can I show
you something real quick?

03:49.630 --> 03:50.696
Not now!

03:50.698 --> 03:52.331
Listen, um, mr. Howell is lost.

03:52.466 --> 03:53.831
Could you please
show him to the door?

03:53.867 --> 03:55.601
I've gotta get on the air.
Thanks for comin' by.

03:55.736 --> 03:56.668
Scott: Think about it!

03:56.704 --> 03:57.869
[sighs]

03:57.938 --> 04:00.005
Mr. Howell!
I'm, uh, mike, junior.

04:00.074 --> 04:02.006
Please, no "mr. Howell"!
I wear cowboy boots.

04:02.042 --> 04:03.475
Call me scott!

04:03.477 --> 04:05.076
Hey, wha--
what have you got here?

04:05.145 --> 04:08.680
Oh, I-- just this stupid little
thing I was thinkin' up, but...

04:08.716 --> 04:10.815
Yeah, I want to
hear all about it.

04:10.884 --> 04:12.551
-Really?
-Yeah.

04:12.686 --> 04:14.953
Okay, uh,
it's a mobile broadcasting unit,

04:15.088 --> 04:17.855
But it's in the shape
of a giant boombox, right?

04:17.891 --> 04:19.691
We're gonna launch it
when the pope comes.

04:19.760 --> 04:21.493
That is wild!

04:21.562 --> 04:23.028
Far out!

04:23.163 --> 04:25.564
Do you mind
if I hold onto this, kid?

04:25.566 --> 04:27.032
Please, take it!
Yeah, yeah.

04:27.034 --> 04:28.700
Thanks.

04:28.702 --> 04:33.005
And if, uh, you ever get sick
of workin' in this museum,

04:33.140 --> 04:35.941
Gimme a shout.

04:35.943 --> 04:37.542
Radio's for the young, kid.

04:37.544 --> 04:41.713
Monogrammed.

04:41.782 --> 04:43.515
Cool.

04:46.186 --> 04:48.086
Fox: Are you sure
you're up for this?

04:48.221 --> 04:50.055
You can't handle gym class
on the best of days.

04:50.190 --> 04:51.456
Oh...

04:51.492 --> 04:53.458
Was the sun always this bright?

04:53.494 --> 04:54.926
Mark, if you're
too sick for laps,

04:54.995 --> 04:56.661
You're too sick for the pope.

04:56.730 --> 04:59.064
Oh, come on.
He has to read one stupid line.

04:59.199 --> 05:00.732
Anyone could do that.

05:00.768 --> 05:02.534
I'd like to see you try.

05:02.669 --> 05:03.801
[coughs]

05:03.803 --> 05:05.737
Are you sure you're okay?

05:05.806 --> 05:07.672
Tina: Ew!
Are you gonna hurl?

05:07.807 --> 05:08.807
[sneezes]

05:08.876 --> 05:10.409
Gross.
Snots.

05:10.544 --> 05:11.943
[whistle blows]

05:12.012 --> 05:13.812
Mr. Byrne: Alright, listen up!

05:13.947 --> 05:15.880
Let's hustle!
[claps hands]

05:15.916 --> 05:16.948
Ugh...

05:17.084 --> 05:18.216
Ten laps!

05:18.252 --> 05:19.217
[everyone sighs]

05:19.286 --> 05:22.154
Today, people!

05:22.289 --> 05:25.090
Come on, critch!

05:25.092 --> 05:26.625
Come on, come on!

05:26.760 --> 05:28.760
C'mon, lift those legs,
lift those legs!

05:28.762 --> 05:30.128
In through the nose...
[inhales]

05:30.130 --> 05:31.163
Exhale.
[exhales]

05:31.298 --> 05:32.931
In...
[inhales]

05:33.000 --> 05:34.232
Mark: Oh...

05:34.301 --> 05:35.500
Middle fox: [laughs]

05:35.635 --> 05:37.969
Critches get stitches!

05:38.038 --> 05:40.171
Adult mark:<i> My own doctor</i>
<i> had labelled me a liar.</i>

05:40.207 --> 05:41.940
<i> So I sought out</i>
<i> a second opinion.</i>

05:42.009 --> 05:44.042
Asthma, epilepsy...

05:44.111 --> 05:45.143
Gout?

05:45.212 --> 05:46.912
That's a self-diagnosis.

05:46.914 --> 05:48.646
It explains my grade in gym.

05:48.782 --> 05:50.815
Where are your parents?

05:50.851 --> 05:53.585
My family doctor says
I'm a hypochondriac,

05:53.587 --> 05:54.786
Which sickens me.

05:54.822 --> 05:56.755
Stop talking.
Just cough.

05:56.757 --> 05:59.057
[coughs]

05:59.126 --> 06:00.725
Hm.
Breathe?

06:00.794 --> 06:03.128
-[breathes in shakily]
-mm.

06:03.130 --> 06:04.662
Give it to me straight, doc.

06:04.732 --> 06:06.097
Well, you're most certainly
not faking.

06:06.166 --> 06:07.632
You have bronchitis.

06:07.634 --> 06:08.767
Would you like
a note for school?

06:08.902 --> 06:10.268
No!

06:10.270 --> 06:12.070
I just need something to
get me through the week.

06:12.205 --> 06:13.805
You know, b-12 shot?

06:13.807 --> 06:15.073
Morphine?

06:15.208 --> 06:17.242
How about some cough syrup?

06:17.244 --> 06:18.843
Oh...

06:24.017 --> 06:25.817
Mary: I just got a phone call.

06:25.819 --> 06:28.920
Who the frig is dr. Lee?

06:28.956 --> 06:30.889
He's my personal physician.

06:30.891 --> 06:32.757
It's private.

06:32.760 --> 06:34.693
Get in bed!

06:34.695 --> 06:37.895
♪

06:41.068 --> 06:42.267
Adult mark:<i> The big day!</i>

06:42.336 --> 06:44.102
<i> My tv debut.</i>

06:44.104 --> 06:46.938
<i> But first, a performance</i>
<i> for a smaller audience.</i>

06:47.007 --> 06:49.240
[hoarsely] woke up
feeling like a new man!

06:49.309 --> 06:50.975
No.
You're staying home.

06:51.110 --> 06:53.712
But I have a duty
to a higher power!

06:53.847 --> 06:54.979
Mike?

06:55.015 --> 06:56.314
-Listen to your mother.
-[phone ringing]

06:56.350 --> 06:58.183
Mary: I already called
the school to let them know

06:58.252 --> 06:59.183
You're not doing your reading.

06:59.219 --> 07:01.319
What?!
[coughing]

07:01.388 --> 07:03.722
-But I'm fine!
-[phone ringing]

07:03.857 --> 07:04.989
Mike sr: Would
somebody get that?

07:05.025 --> 07:06.057
Mike jr: Yeah, got it!

07:06.126 --> 07:08.393
Yeah, me and the b'ys,
we're selling pope crap

07:08.395 --> 07:09.928
To raise money for our bar.

07:09.997 --> 07:11.730
What do you think?

07:11.865 --> 07:13.165
What is that?

07:13.300 --> 07:14.633
Pop: "pope on a rope"!

07:14.768 --> 07:16.201
How much would you pay for this?

07:16.203 --> 07:18.370
That is my good avon soap!

07:18.372 --> 07:20.672
No, it's not!
It just looks like it.

07:20.741 --> 07:23.275
Anyway, I've got two dozen
more setting over here.

07:23.277 --> 07:24.609
Mark: Ah, yes, I'll help--

07:24.744 --> 07:26.811
You are gonna sit on the couch
and watch tv.

07:26.880 --> 07:28.146
You're gettin' on my last nerve!

07:28.281 --> 07:29.247
Mark: Ohhh!

07:29.316 --> 07:31.148
All the times I pray to be sick!

07:31.185 --> 07:32.350
What kind of god is this?

07:32.386 --> 07:34.619
Mary: Get!

07:34.688 --> 07:36.020
Mike jr: Yes, sir.

07:36.056 --> 07:38.189
Thank you, sir!

07:38.258 --> 07:39.824
[hangs up phone]

07:39.893 --> 07:41.993
That was scott howell.

07:42.062 --> 07:44.596
He just offered me
a job at voaq radio.

07:44.665 --> 07:45.697
[sighs]

07:45.766 --> 07:48.299
He's only hiring you
to get at me!

07:48.368 --> 07:50.368
Or, you know,
maybe he thinks I'm good?

07:50.404 --> 07:52.437
No, that's not it!

07:52.439 --> 07:55.706
I turned him down.

07:55.742 --> 07:57.242
I'm taking the job.

07:57.244 --> 07:59.978
♪

08:03.417 --> 08:06.985
Mark is off sick so we will
have to select another student.

08:06.987 --> 08:08.687
Sister rose: Perhaps
I should have chosen

08:08.822 --> 08:10.922
Sister maura's class.

08:10.991 --> 08:15.927
Maybe this illness
is a sign of god's disapproval.

08:16.062 --> 08:19.598
Fox: But, sister,
didn't jesus say something about

08:19.733 --> 08:23.701
Not throwing stones...?

08:23.770 --> 08:25.169
You're right.

08:25.205 --> 08:27.472
God loves redemption.

08:27.474 --> 08:30.742
You can redeem yourself by
doing the reading for the pope.

08:30.811 --> 08:32.110
-Ms. Fowler: Pardon?
-Fox: What?

08:32.245 --> 08:33.678
Good luck, ms. Fowler.

08:33.813 --> 08:37.215
I'm sure fox
will make you proud.

08:37.350 --> 08:38.783
Middle fox: [laughs]

08:38.819 --> 08:40.352
Tv: This was
the scene earlier...

08:40.487 --> 08:42.253
Mark: My big break!

08:42.289 --> 08:43.622
Millions watching!

08:43.757 --> 08:45.023
The adrenaline
would get me through!

08:45.025 --> 08:46.358
Maybe I can still make it!

08:46.493 --> 08:48.893
You're not getting off this
couch until you feel better.

08:48.896 --> 08:51.195
[coughing]

08:51.265 --> 08:52.964
Oh...

08:52.966 --> 08:56.167
Asthma, epilepsy, bronchitis...

08:56.203 --> 08:57.702
Sin.

08:57.837 --> 09:00.271
You never had a chance.

09:00.340 --> 09:03.308
Tv: The pope's schedule
is packed with stops

09:03.377 --> 09:04.642
Along the newfoundland shore.

09:04.778 --> 09:07.178
Adult mark:<i> There was still</i>
<i> a way to get to the pope.</i>

09:07.247 --> 09:08.780
<i> A very catholic way...</i>

09:08.849 --> 09:09.914
<i> Guilt.</i>

09:09.983 --> 09:11.783
[coughs]

09:11.852 --> 09:13.652
You're right!

09:13.787 --> 09:17.122
I wish I was there
to be blessed.

09:17.257 --> 09:20.925
Tv: A blessing could
mean a miracle cure.

09:21.061 --> 09:23.127
I might have a chance then.
[coughs]

09:23.196 --> 09:26.264
Tv: In search
of hope and healing,

09:26.399 --> 09:28.466
A record crowd
has gathered to see--

09:28.535 --> 09:30.001
Get in the car.

09:30.037 --> 09:31.970
-Oh, yes!
-What?

09:32.039 --> 09:34.339
I just... Hope this works.

09:34.408 --> 09:36.173
[coughs]
yeah.

09:40.681 --> 09:42.614
Adult mark:<i> Pop and his buddies</i>
<i> turned the papal visit</i>

09:42.616 --> 09:44.081
<i> Into a mini las vegas!</i>

09:44.117 --> 09:46.217
Father handrigan: Four quarters
holding up the wheel!

09:46.219 --> 09:48.486
Anybody, four quarters?
Come get your tickets!

09:48.522 --> 09:53.758
See, state of the art!
Everything in here is digital.

09:53.893 --> 09:56.828
Bet you never seen
anything like this at vocm.

09:56.897 --> 09:59.864
No.
No, nothin'!

09:59.866 --> 10:02.300
Wait, no, the super roving radio
looks pretty cool, right?

10:02.369 --> 10:03.401
Scott: Ah...

10:03.437 --> 10:05.236
Mike sr: And here we are,
pope-side,

10:05.272 --> 10:07.304
Here at what is quickly
becoming quite the event...

10:07.341 --> 10:09.440
Yeah, it's not as cool
as ours, though!

10:09.476 --> 10:12.510
[electric guitar playing]

10:12.512 --> 10:14.312
Maybe I shouldn't have
showed you their design.

10:14.381 --> 10:16.715
Poppycock!

10:16.850 --> 10:19.484
Here, I have something for ya.

10:19.553 --> 10:21.352
Look at this bad boy.

10:21.421 --> 10:26.324
-Oh, come on!
-Yeah.

10:26.459 --> 10:27.992
Mike sr: Good god!

10:28.061 --> 10:29.794
He's wearing enemy colours!

10:29.830 --> 10:32.863
[ominous rock sting]

10:36.203 --> 10:37.936
I can't do this!
It's stupid.

10:37.938 --> 10:39.137
There's too many people.

10:39.206 --> 10:40.538
Ritche: You're just nervous.

10:40.540 --> 10:42.907
Whenever I'm scared
of public speaking,

10:42.909 --> 10:45.577
I picture the audience
in their underwear.

10:45.579 --> 10:48.813
Just picture the pope
in his underwear.

10:48.948 --> 10:50.881
Ew, gross!

10:50.917 --> 10:52.217
Ugh!

10:52.352 --> 10:54.485
No help.

10:59.225 --> 11:02.560
Quick blessing,
straight back to bed.

11:02.596 --> 11:05.162
Just know, it's not
your fault that I'm weak.

11:05.198 --> 11:06.964
It's just bad genes.

11:06.966 --> 11:09.000
I made ya!
Whose fault is it, then, hm?

11:09.069 --> 11:10.168
Dad's.

11:10.303 --> 11:11.969
Oof, I'd say, yeah.

11:12.039 --> 11:12.971
[turns on radio]

11:13.106 --> 11:15.239
Mike sr: [radio] we go now
live to flatrock,

11:15.275 --> 11:17.375
Where the pope is about
to bless the fishing fleet.

11:17.444 --> 11:23.114
Let's listen in...

11:23.116 --> 11:27.218
Pope: [radio] the joyful event
that unites us is the blessing

11:27.287 --> 11:30.522
Of the fishing fleet
here at flatrock.

11:30.657 --> 11:33.992
That jesus called
simon, peter...

11:34.127 --> 11:38.663
Why don't we show your old man
what you're made out of, huh?

11:38.665 --> 11:40.397
Hey...

11:40.434 --> 11:42.267
Scram.

11:42.402 --> 11:44.002
Yeah.

11:44.004 --> 11:47.071
She's all yours.

11:47.107 --> 11:49.207
Sailor: [on news]
thank you, holy father.

11:49.209 --> 11:51.609
On behalf of all the fishermen,

11:51.611 --> 11:53.878
We also wish you
a blessed and safe journey.

11:54.013 --> 11:55.446
Over.

11:55.449 --> 11:57.515
And the pope has blessed
the newfoundland fishing fleet.

11:57.650 --> 11:59.917
Mike jr: You're listening
to voaq radio.

11:59.986 --> 12:03.554
Call in for your chance to win
vip tickets to pope on the rock!

12:03.590 --> 12:05.090
That little judas!

12:05.225 --> 12:07.158
Mike jr: Call in
to our request line

12:07.194 --> 12:09.894
And tell us your
biggest sin to win!

12:09.930 --> 12:12.464
Dick, turn up our volume.

12:12.599 --> 12:15.500
-Are you sure?
-Just do it!

12:15.569 --> 12:17.568
[music turns up]

12:17.637 --> 12:21.505
<i> ♪ if you're a part of</i>
<i> the wide world of vocm... ♪</i>

12:23.176 --> 12:24.575
Stand up straight.
Stand up.

12:24.644 --> 12:26.377
Come on, stand straight.
Do up that button.

12:26.513 --> 12:28.646
Zipper!

12:28.715 --> 12:31.049
Has anyone seen fox?

12:31.184 --> 12:32.417
Um...

12:32.419 --> 12:34.719
I think she may have
pipped off?

12:34.721 --> 12:36.287
Pipped off?!

12:36.323 --> 12:38.456
Oh, typical.

12:38.525 --> 12:41.258
[exhales]

12:41.294 --> 12:43.060
Mike sr: [radio]
motorists should be warned

12:43.096 --> 12:48.232
The pope is leaving the area,
so all roads are now closed.

12:48.301 --> 12:49.934
Act like you're having
an asthma attack!

12:50.003 --> 12:51.135
What, why?

12:51.138 --> 12:52.337
You've been faking sick
your whole life!

12:52.472 --> 12:53.705
Do it!

12:53.707 --> 12:55.673
Adult mark:<i> It was time</i>
<i> to use my faking superpower</i>

12:55.742 --> 12:56.641
<i> For good.</i>

12:56.776 --> 12:58.142
Road's closed.

12:58.145 --> 12:59.377
Mark: [gasping]

12:59.379 --> 13:01.145
Can't... Breathe...

13:01.214 --> 13:04.148
[gasping]
is this... The light?

13:04.217 --> 13:06.951
Can you see that my son
is having an asthma attack?

13:07.086 --> 13:11.622
So help me, if my little boy
dies in this car, you're next!

13:11.658 --> 13:13.992
We're gonna let her through!

13:14.127 --> 13:16.294
["all I need is a miracle" by
mike & the mechanics playing]

13:16.296 --> 13:17.662
Go on, let her through!
Let her through!

13:17.664 --> 13:19.297
<i> ♪ all I need is a miracle ♪</i>

13:19.366 --> 13:21.098
Officer: Gordie,
get her an escort, would ya?

13:21.134 --> 13:23.101
<i> ♪ all I need is you ♪</i>

13:23.103 --> 13:24.569
Let's go, get her through!

13:24.638 --> 13:27.238
<i> ♪ all I need is a miracle ♪</i>

13:27.274 --> 13:29.040
<i> ♪ all I need is you ♪</i>

13:29.109 --> 13:31.642
[siren wailing]

13:31.678 --> 13:34.579
<i> ♪ all I need is a miracle... ♪</i>

13:34.714 --> 13:37.248
Adult mark:<i> We followed</i>
<i> the pope like pilgrims.</i>

13:37.284 --> 13:40.752
<i> Not since the virgin mary</i>
<i>was there such a dedicated mom.</i>

13:40.754 --> 13:42.987
<i> And once we cleared</i>
<i> the barricade,</i>

13:43.122 --> 13:46.523
<i> Mom ditched our police escort</i>
<i> like a bad habit.</i>

13:46.560 --> 13:49.060
[laughs]

13:49.062 --> 13:51.029
[coughs]

13:51.164 --> 13:52.397
Excellent work.

13:52.532 --> 13:54.399
Adult mark:<i> Who needed</i>
<i> faith in god?</i>

13:54.534 --> 13:59.137
<i> I had faith in mom.</i>

13:59.139 --> 14:00.438
Pop: Beautiful stuff.

14:00.573 --> 14:02.006
Yeah, beautiful.

14:02.075 --> 14:04.275
So, souvenirs!
Souvenirs here!

14:04.410 --> 14:07.345
Come get your
john paul ii souvenirs!

14:07.414 --> 14:08.646
Great, great.

14:08.715 --> 14:11.082
Oh!
Oh, here.

14:11.217 --> 14:14.485
Pope: ...Man and woman
who are...

14:14.621 --> 14:16.754
Oh, bless this, father.

14:16.823 --> 14:18.155
Oh yeah, here.

14:18.191 --> 14:19.490
Get that water.
Bless it there.

14:19.559 --> 14:20.591
Get it in there.

14:20.660 --> 14:22.360
Beautiful.

14:22.362 --> 14:26.231
Pope: ...Love and protect
those who use them.

14:26.366 --> 14:28.633
Rosaries!
Rosaries for sale!

14:28.702 --> 14:31.302
Blessed by the holiness himself!

14:31.437 --> 14:34.372
And holy, holy, holy water!

14:34.374 --> 14:37.308
It's so holy you can
practically walk on it!

14:37.310 --> 14:39.243
Pop: Come on, now!
There you go!

14:39.245 --> 14:41.346
Yes, please!
Very good choice.

14:41.348 --> 14:43.781
Very good choice.
Yeah, beautiful.

14:43.850 --> 14:46.183
Thank you, thank you.
Thank you, that's perfect.

14:46.219 --> 14:48.252
Well, this is [inaudible]...

14:48.388 --> 14:51.122
♪

14:51.191 --> 14:55.727
♪

14:55.862 --> 14:57.195
Ritche: Where are you going?

14:57.330 --> 14:59.130
That nun set me up!

14:59.265 --> 15:02.333
There will literally be people
in poland calling me a nimrod!

15:02.369 --> 15:04.335
If you don't do it,

15:04.470 --> 15:07.739
You'll be proving everyone
who says you can't right.

15:07.874 --> 15:10.675
You got this.

15:10.677 --> 15:14.545
If this sucks,
you're dead, okay?

15:14.581 --> 15:17.081
Yeah.
I know.

15:21.521 --> 15:22.620
Pop: Souvenirs!

15:22.755 --> 15:24.288
John paul ii souvenirs!

15:24.290 --> 15:26.157
Come get your souvenirs!

15:26.226 --> 15:28.292
-Oh, oh.
-Excuse me.

15:28.295 --> 15:32.830
Sorry, father.

15:32.965 --> 15:35.766
I'll take two rosaries
and a "pope on a rope."

15:35.835 --> 15:38.303
Oh!
What a good choice, father.

15:38.438 --> 15:40.171
Well, here, take these rosaries.

15:40.173 --> 15:41.606
There we are for you.

15:41.741 --> 15:43.307
And there's the pope on a rope.

15:43.310 --> 15:44.375
Beautiful.

15:44.377 --> 15:46.110
Happy scrubbing, father.

15:46.179 --> 15:48.312
Thank you.
Special rate for the clergy.

15:48.348 --> 15:51.182
[chuckles]
thank you.

15:51.251 --> 15:52.550
Thank you.

15:52.552 --> 15:54.485
Tv: And now a reading
from a local student

15:54.521 --> 15:56.620
From st. Bridget's school.

16:00.293 --> 16:01.726
Adult mark:<i> And there he was.</i>

16:01.795 --> 16:03.661
<i> The catholic elvis!</i>

16:03.730 --> 16:06.430
<i> I was seconds away</i>
<i> from international fame!</i>

16:06.499 --> 16:08.299
This is it!

16:08.368 --> 16:11.869
A reading from
the book of matthew.

16:11.905 --> 16:13.804
I'm too late!

16:13.940 --> 16:15.906
And jesus said to them,

16:15.942 --> 16:20.812
"follow me and I will make you
become fishers of men."

16:20.814 --> 16:23.348
Audience: Amen.
[applause]

16:23.483 --> 16:25.349
Adult mark:<i> I may have</i>
<i> missed my chance,</i>

16:25.352 --> 16:28.886
<i> But watching fox, I wouldn't</i>
<i> want it any other way.</i>

16:28.888 --> 16:31.355
-[applause]
-ritche: Yeah!

16:31.358 --> 16:33.424
Mike sr: [radio] and that was
a reading from a student

16:33.460 --> 16:35.626
At st. Bridget's.
My son mark goes there...

16:35.762 --> 16:37.762
I'm sorry you
didn't get to go up.

16:37.764 --> 16:39.497
Mike sr: [radio] luckily,
we'll be broadcasting

16:39.632 --> 16:40.765
Right up to the minute...

16:40.767 --> 16:43.234
It's okay.

16:43.303 --> 16:46.437
This is even better.

16:46.473 --> 16:48.772
It's more about the journey,
ya know?

16:48.808 --> 16:52.777
[radio playing
in the background]

16:52.779 --> 16:54.378
Mike sr: [radio] mike critch,
reporting live

16:54.447 --> 16:58.349
From the tailgate party.

16:58.351 --> 16:59.884
All hands are
listening to ye crowd.

16:59.886 --> 17:01.452
Way to go, young fella.

17:01.521 --> 17:03.320
Thanks, dick.

17:03.390 --> 17:07.625
Hey, did my dad say anything?

17:07.627 --> 17:09.627
Look, his heart
might be broke right now,

17:09.629 --> 17:11.195
But he'll get over it.

17:11.330 --> 17:12.463
Broke?

17:12.465 --> 17:15.299
I get it.
You do what you gotta do!

17:15.435 --> 17:18.136
But... By the way,

17:18.271 --> 17:20.571
Would you give
my resume to scott?

17:20.607 --> 17:23.741
Us young fellas got to
stick together now.

17:23.743 --> 17:24.776
Yeah.

17:24.911 --> 17:26.677
I better get back to the booth

17:26.713 --> 17:28.312
Before your dad
realizes I'm gone.

17:28.381 --> 17:29.580
Scott!

17:29.715 --> 17:31.282
Mike sr: [radio] we're expecting
to see the weather

17:31.351 --> 17:32.316
Turn to rain showers soon,

17:32.385 --> 17:34.685
So if you're out to
have a gawk at the pope,

17:34.754 --> 17:36.954
Make sure you bring
an umbrella or a rain hat!

17:37.023 --> 17:40.224
The pontiff is expected to
leave newfoundland around 7 pm,

17:40.359 --> 17:42.460
Making a quick stop in toronto
before heading home

17:42.529 --> 17:44.295
To vatican city
to put his feet up.

17:44.430 --> 17:45.763
We can go home.

17:45.765 --> 17:48.466
Aw.

17:48.468 --> 17:49.567
[loud feedback]

17:49.636 --> 17:53.771
Jesus christ!

17:53.773 --> 17:55.573
...Is, uh, certainly
a newfoundlander today.

17:55.642 --> 17:59.243
After all, he was a...
Fisherman.

17:59.378 --> 18:03.414
Dick: And a good fisherman
at that, mike!

18:03.483 --> 18:05.415
You're listening to vocm.

18:05.452 --> 18:07.784
With live coverage as the pope
makes his final journey

18:07.821 --> 18:10.288
Back to the airport, then home.

18:10.290 --> 18:12.857
Oh, that pope gets around worse
than mary packin' magdalene!

18:12.859 --> 18:14.792
Adult mark:<i> The pope</i>
<i> was done with newfoundland,</i>

18:14.861 --> 18:16.594
<i> But mom was not</i>
<i> done with the pope.</i>

18:16.596 --> 18:17.795
Mark: Aah!

18:17.797 --> 18:19.930
Mary: Hold on, we're not through
with this yet, by jesus!

18:19.966 --> 18:21.933
That was a pretty good
first day of radio, son.

18:22.068 --> 18:24.001
-Oh! Thanks, man.
-Yeah.

18:24.037 --> 18:25.937
So, what time tomorrow?

18:26.072 --> 18:27.271
Oh... Yeah!

18:27.406 --> 18:30.541
See, I don't know if we have any
slots open for you right now,

18:30.676 --> 18:32.710
But we'll-- we'll find
something down the line.

18:32.779 --> 18:35.012
Hey, scott, thank you very much
for the opportunity.

18:35.014 --> 18:36.214
Uh-huh.

18:36.216 --> 18:38.516
Mike jr: But you were just
using me to get to my dad.

18:38.518 --> 18:39.516
So, I quit.

18:39.552 --> 18:40.551
What?!
You--

18:40.587 --> 18:42.853
You can't qui--
you can't go back to vocm!

18:42.889 --> 18:45.356
They're a bunch of losers!

18:45.358 --> 18:48.292
Ah... That's weird.
I guess I am too, then.

18:48.328 --> 18:50.427
-Alright.
-Well, you-- you can't quit,

18:50.497 --> 18:53.864
Because I fire you!
You're fired.

18:53.867 --> 18:55.900
Okay.

18:55.902 --> 18:58.469
By the way, there's been
three minutes of dead air

18:58.471 --> 18:59.369
On your station.

18:59.405 --> 19:02.573
Yeah, I-I turned it off
when I quit, so...

19:02.642 --> 19:04.708
What...?
You can't do that in radio!

19:04.744 --> 19:06.344
-Yeah.
-You have no respect!

19:06.346 --> 19:07.578
Mike jr: I'm still learning.

19:07.713 --> 19:09.780
-You son of a--
-critch?

19:09.782 --> 19:12.783
Scott: You have
no respect for radio!

19:12.785 --> 19:14.519
♪

19:14.654 --> 19:15.987
Mike sr: [tv]
breaking pope news!

19:16.122 --> 19:19.323
A slight diversion for the pope
on his way to the airport.

19:19.458 --> 19:21.959
A group of polish fishermen
are in port.

19:21.961 --> 19:23.928
They'd hoped to meet
his holiness.

19:24.063 --> 19:26.264
He is the first polish pope,

19:26.399 --> 19:28.465
And it seems
the holy father will stop

19:28.467 --> 19:30.468
To offer the fishermen
a blessing on his way...

19:30.470 --> 19:33.003
Adult mark:<i> Mom had brought me</i>
<i> to half the doctors in town,</i>

19:33.072 --> 19:36.974
<i> So why not try a faith healer?</i>

19:37.043 --> 19:40.044
-[brakes screech]
-mary: Gotcha, ha!

19:40.113 --> 19:42.947
Adult mark:<i> What mother</i>
<i> could resist a miracle cure?</i>

19:43.016 --> 19:44.882
Mary: Come on, sweetheart,
let's go!

19:44.884 --> 19:46.350
Excuse me, get out of the way!

19:46.485 --> 19:50.687
Deathly ill child
coming through!

19:50.723 --> 19:51.689
Bless my son.

19:51.824 --> 19:54.058
Bless my son for the asthma.

19:54.193 --> 19:56.627
And for the epilepsy.

19:56.629 --> 19:59.830
Oh, thank your holiness.

19:59.899 --> 20:01.498
Come on.

20:01.534 --> 20:03.434
Let's get you back in the car
before you catch

20:03.436 --> 20:04.835
Your death again.
Excuse me.

20:04.904 --> 20:06.770
Adult mark:<i> Turns out</i>
<i> there are many ways</i>

20:06.806 --> 20:07.905
<i> To say "I love you."</i>

20:08.040 --> 20:10.507
<i> Sometimes it's how far</i>
<i> a person will go for you.</i>

20:10.543 --> 20:12.509
Mike sr: [radio]
and now newfoundland bids

20:12.545 --> 20:15.346
A fond farewell
to pope john paul ii.

20:15.481 --> 20:16.513
Adult mark:<i> And sometimes...</i>

20:16.549 --> 20:19.650
<i> It's where they're</i>
<i> willing to meet you</i> .

20:19.686 --> 20:23.854
♪

20:23.990 --> 20:27.325
I know I got a lot to learn.

20:27.460 --> 20:29.993
I could learn
a bit from you too.

20:30.029 --> 20:33.430
You did a great job today.

20:33.466 --> 20:37.134
♪

20:37.136 --> 20:39.470
♪

20:39.605 --> 20:41.505
Come on.

20:47.614 --> 20:50.348
Tv: Newfoundlanders will
remember this special visit

20:50.483 --> 20:52.783
For years to come.

20:52.785 --> 20:54.585
Pop: Woo!
Over 800!

20:54.720 --> 20:56.020
We've got enough for the bar!

20:56.022 --> 20:59.623
That is indeed a miracle!
[chuckles]

20:59.625 --> 21:01.892
[coughs]
oh, dear.

21:02.027 --> 21:03.861
Maybe we should have
got one more blessing.

21:03.930 --> 21:04.995
Mary: Oh...

21:05.064 --> 21:08.699
My biggest blessing
is right here.

21:08.768 --> 21:10.768
[coughing]

21:10.770 --> 21:12.436
[coughing]

21:12.472 --> 21:14.572
Mary... I'm sick.

21:14.574 --> 21:17.574
Jesus murphy!

21:17.644 --> 21:20.778
[all coughing]

21:20.913 --> 21:23.047
-Mary!
-Tea?

21:23.049 --> 21:26.783
♪

21:26.819 --> 21:30.588
♪

21:30.723 --> 21:35.660
♪

21:35.795 --> 21:41.399
♪

21:41.534 --> 21:45.002
♪

21:45.071 --> 21:50.040
♪
